    "description": "Created by a guy with a knack for big numbers and a vendetta against pests, comes an incremental clicker/idler that takes a different approach on progress: No prestige mechanic.<h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Features of the game include, but not limited to.</strong></h2><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Strategic attacking is rewarded and clients pay more for a job well done!<br></li><li> Numerous achievements to be gotten for those who enjoy them!<br></li><li> Destroy pests any way you can with whatever weapons you acquire.<br></li><li> Swarms of bugs, special glowing bugs with extra rewards.<br></li><li> No prestige mechanic, so your progress will always increment.<br></li><li> Costs of items, upgrades and values were simulated and tested and values are not arbitrary.<br></li><li> Very few people actually read these text descriptions, and if you did, the next line will surprise you<br></li><li> Set your company name to &quot;Thoroughly Inc.&quot; to get a nice 2500 coins to upgrade your first weapon right away.<br></li><li> Still reading?  Making your name &quot;Reader&quot; will also unlock the sticky trap for the first level.<br></li><li> Just how far does it go?  Who knows, perhaps you'll find out.</li></ul><br>Your play style is your choice.  An armada of bugs are awaiting their annihilation!<br>If you choose to idle, there are numerous traps you can set to encourage critters to sniff it out and find out what's really inside.  (It's not candy).<br><br>Additional note: While the game isn't a Virtual Reality game - it seems to work with the Quest 2 VR headset and is quite fun in that mode!",
